quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  14,1,"Alif Lām Ra. A Scripture that We sent down to you<sup>sg </sup><i>, </i>that you may bring mankind out from darkness<i>(es) </i>into light—by the leave of their Lord—to the path of the Almighty, the Praiseworthy:"
  14,2,"Allah{1}—the One to Whom belongs whatever isin the heavens and whatever is in the earth. And woe to the deniers from a severe punishment!",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Nafie’, Ibn Amer and Abu Ja’far read it as: “(He is) Allah—the One to whom…” Roways read it as such only when he connected signs 1 and 2.]
  14,3,"Those who seek the love of the Earlier Life more than the Hereafter, and bar<i>(people) </i>from the way of Allah and seek to make it crooked—those are in extreme misguidance."
  14,4,"And never did We send any messenger but<i>(he spoke) </i>in the tongue of his people, that he may clarify for them. Then Allah leads astray whom He wills and guides whom He wills, for He is the Almighty, the All-Wise."
  14,5,"And very truly We sent Moses with Our signs: “Bring your<sup>sg </sup>people out of darkness<i>(es) </i>into light and remind them of the Days of Allah{1}.” Indeed, in that are signs for everyone who is most patient, constantly thankful.”",footnotes:1:[A grammatical shift from 3<sup>rd</sup> person to 2 person to 2<sup>nd</sup> person. person.]
